//✅ 6. The "Anti-Scam" Logic (TTL)
This is a critical "Defensive" feature.

Scenario: "How do you prevent me from buying an item that was already sold or is expired?"


Go to "Post Item" and create a new listing (as Seller A).

Immediately go to the "Messages" tab (as Buyer B).

Find the "Unread" badge or notification for a new message on that listing.

Attempt to Open Chat.

Expected Result: The app should show a modal: "Listing No Longer Available" or "Listing Expired."

Explanation: "Even though the seller posted this 2 minutes ago, we enforce a strict 1-hour Time-to-Live (TTL). The database automatically purges this listing. Since our database is real-time, the chat API cannot access a ghost record, preventing you from entering a conversation about an item that doesn't exist."

✅ 7. The "Silent Worker" (Admin)
This proves the backend is doing heavy lifting without slowing the UI.

Scenario: "While I was browsing, how did you update the listing's status?"


Log in as the Admin (admin@test.com).

Go to "Seeding & Maintenance."

Look for the "Listings Management" or "Cron Simulation" area.

Click "Run TTL Purge & Expiry Check."

You will see the console log show "Running Cron Task" or "Processing TTL Queue."

Immediately switch back to Buyer B and refresh the Home feed.

The item should disappear instantly.
